  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/warm-pepper-lentil-white-bean-salad-with-goats-cheese/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/warm-pepper-lentil-white-bean-salad-with-goats-cheese/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pan is hot, add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the shallot has softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/warm-pepper-lentil-white-bean-salad-with-goats-cheese/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your<strong> sweet pointed pepper[s]</strong> into rings</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Drain and rinse your<strong> green lentils</strong> and <strong>cannellini beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/warm-pepper-lentil-white-bean-salad-with-goats-cheese/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced peppers </strong>to the pan along with your <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>garlic paste</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the peppers are beginning to soften</p><p>Once soft, add the <strong>drained lentils & cannellini beans</strong> and cook for 1 min further or until everything is warmed through</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/warm-pepper-lentil-white-bean-salad-with-goats-cheese/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Crumble your <strong>goats' cheese</strong> into rough bite-sized pieces</p><p>Cut your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> into 2 wedges per person</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/warm-pepper-lentil-white-bean-salad-with-goats-cheese/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon wedge[s]</strong> with your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>in a small bowl – this is your <strong>zesty</strong> <strong>dressing</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>zesty</strong> <strong>dressing</strong> to the pan with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped parsley </strong>(save the rest for garnish!)<strong> </strong>and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>warm</strong> <strong>pepper, lentil & white bean salad</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/warm-pepper-lentil-white-bean-salad-with-goats-cheese/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>warm</strong> <strong>pepper, lentil & white bean salad</strong> with the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> and<strong> salad </strong>over the top</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped parsley</strong>, a <strong>lemon wedge </strong>and an extra drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Sprinkle over your<strong> goats'</strong> <strong>cheese</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
